};

using Drawable = folly::Poly<IDrawable>;

int main() {
  Drawable obj = Circle{};
  obj.draw(std::cout);
}
```

Uncommenting any `noexcept` breaks on my machine (using clang from 2017-11-25 and folly from 2017-12-25)

I attached the error message for uncommenting `Circle::draw`'s  `noexcept` specifier.

[error.log](https://github.com/facebook/folly/files/1639659/error.log)

Would it make sense to create a construct StreamingPromise that can `setValue` multiple times? The use case is that when the call site is something like:

